---
description: Git commit messages and pull request text must be written in English.
alwaysApply: true
---

# Git and pull requests — English only

- Write **all commit messages** (subject and body) in **English**: clear, imperative mood for the subject where conventional commits are used (e.g. `feat: add admin catalog preview`).
- Write **all pull request titles and descriptions** in **English** (summary, testing steps, checklist notes, reviewer comments intended for the PR thread).
- Jira / internal ticket IDs (e.g. CF4-88) may appear alongside English text.
- UI copy, user-facing strings, and team chat may follow other language preferences; this rule applies specifically to **Git history and GitHub/GitLab PR artifacts**.
